238.question: What is the performance of the model?

5-Table2-1.png: The performance of the model is measured by accuracy (ACC), F1 score for the positive class (F1 pos), and F1 score for the negative class (F1 neg). The table shows that the model achieved an accuracy of 0.99 on clean test data, indicating a high level of performance. Additionally, the F1 scores for both classes are also quite high, with F1 pos at 0.99 and F1 neg at 0.98. This suggests that the model is highly accurate in predicting both positive and negative classes.
5-Figure2-1.png: Line 1 and line 3 begin at the same point, then line 1 decreases to a lower ylabel value than line 3. Line 2 begins at a higher ylabel value than line 1 and line 3, but ends at a lower ylabel value than line 1.

238.answer:
Experiment 1: ACC around 0.5 with 50% noise rate in worst case - clearly higher than baselines for all noise rates
Experiment 2: ACC on real noisy datasets: 0.7 on Movie, 0.79 on Laptop, 0.86 on Restaurant (clearly higher than baselines in almost all cases)
